  "body": "Textarea values can be set with the \"value\" prop. If this prop is set to null or undefined (such as when resetting an object to clear the form), it will retain the old value. \n\nLooking at the source, it looks like there is some intentional null behavior written in, but it does behave differently from other form elements.\n\njsfiddle demo of the problem: https://jsfiddle.net/0saj7ww7/2/\n",
